<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870224-0112 </DOCNO><HL> Decision/Capital to Buy Firm</HL><DD> 02/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> DCFTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WILMINGTON, Del.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Decision/Capital Fund agreed to acquire closely held Hopper Soliday andamp; Co., a Philadelphia investment banking and brokerage firm, for about $14 million.    Decision/Capital, a closed-end investment fund, said it will pay with a combination of cash and convertible subordinated debentures. It won't issue shares in addition to the 2,005,000 currently outstanding except upon possible conversion of the debentures.    Hopper has a net worth of about $5 million with 1986 revenue exceeding $12 million. Decision has net assets of $37.8 million. </TEXT></DOC>